  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- Sets global standards for combating money laundering\n- Provides recommendations for national legal and regulatory systems\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention against Corruption\n\n3. International Monetary Fund (IMF) Guidelines\n- Provides recommendations for preventing financial crimes\n\n4. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Sets international banking standards to prevent money laundering\n\n5. European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Establish uniform rules across EU member states\n\n6. Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Requires financial institutions to assist government agencies in detecting and preventing money laundering\n\nThese laws typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n- Conduct due diligence\n\nWhile specific implementation varies by country, these international frameworks create a coordinated approach to combating money laundering globally.",
